\title{BCI Hatchery: Skill Inventory}
\taxon{reference}
\import{macros}

\p{The ASI hatchery contains 19 skills with BCI interpretations, organized
by the GF(3) triad: generation (+1), coordination (0), verification (-1).
Each skill maps to a forester tree in the BCI Factory pipeline.}

\subtree{
\title{Dedicated BCI skills (core 4)}

\table{
  \tr{\th{Skill} \th{Trit} \th{Port} \th{Function}}
  \tr{\td{bci-colored-operad} \td{+1} \td{—} \td{VM→Container→Process enclosure, GF(3) neural pathways}}
  \tr{\td{sheaf-cohomology-bci} \td{0} \td{—} \td{Cellular sheaves, Čech cohomology, sheaf Laplacian}}
  \tr{\td{bci-protocols} \td{0} \td{:7069/:7071} \td{Record/replay sessions on bci.red + bci.blue SSE}}
  \tr{\td{bci-red-goblins} \td{-1} \td{:7071} \td{Goblins actors on bci.red, C ABI goblins.zig, CapTP}}
}

\p{These four form the BCI kernel: colored operad generates structure (+1),
sheaf cohomology and protocols coordinate (0), red-goblins verifies capability
security (-1). Sum = #{1 + 0 + 0 - 1 = 0}. Balanced.}
}

